{"id":4531,"date":"2023-12-08T15:32:51","date_gmt":"2023-12-08T04:32:51","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.stokefoiling.com\/?post_type=help_centre&#038;p=4531"},"modified":"2023-12-08T15:35:29","modified_gmt":"2023-12-08T04:35:29","slug":"user-warnings-water-safety","status":"publish","type":"help_centre","link":"https:\/\/www.stokefoiling.com\/help-centre\/safety\/user-warnings-water-safety\/","title":{"rendered":"User Warnings: Water Safety"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>When operating the Stoke Foil Boost, it&#8217;s imperative to exercise caution to ensure a safe and enjoyable experience. First and foremost, users should stay clear of the propeller, as it has no housing to provide protection. This is essential for preventing injuries and maintaining a secure environment during operation.<\/p><p>Additionally, being mindful of your position to breaking waves is crucial. Avoid placing your board with the foil and unit between you and the braking wave to prevent potential collisions and enhance overall safety.<\/p><p>Before initiating the motor, ensure that you start in deep enough water, considering the mast length. Starting in sufficiently deep water will contribute to a smooth and controlled launch.<\/p><p>We highly recommend the use of a coiled leash. Opting for a coiled leash enhances safety by preventing entanglements and ensuring the leash remains manageable during use. This is particularly important in dynamic water conditions.<\/p><p>Always start the motor while on top of your board. This practice ensures you will not be injured by the propeller, which is exposed with no housing.<\/p>","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>When operating the Stoke Foil Boost, it&#8217;s imperative to exercise caution to ensure a safe and enjoyable experience. First and foremost, users should stay clear of the propeller, as it has no housing to provide protection. This is essential for preventing injuries and maintaining a secure environment during operation. Additional